Forecasting Canadian Import Volume

## Project Overview
This project forecasts monthly import volume indexes for selected Canadian commodity groups:
- Furniture and Fixtures
- Clothing and Footwear
- Agricultural Products

The goal is to evaluate different forecasting models and compare their performance.

## Dataset
Source: Statistics Canada  
Period: 2017–2025  
Frequency: Monthly  

## Models Used
- Naïve
- Seasonal Naïve
- Linear Regression (lag features)
- Random Forest
- SARIMA

## Methodology
- Data cleaning and filtering (imports, seasonally adjusted)
- Feature engineering (lags, rolling averages, COVID dummy)
- Train-test split (2017–2023 train, 2024–2025 test)
- Model evaluation using RMSE and MAE

## Key Findings
- Naïve model outperformed all other models
- Advanced models did not improve accuracy
- Weak seasonality and structural breaks impacted performance

## Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas
- Scikit-learn
- Statsmodels

